\sum_{n=1}^{100}n=1+2+3+4 +\dots+100
=100+99+98+\dots+1
\therefore 2 \sum_{n=1}^{100}n=(100+1)+(99+2)+\dots+(1+100)
=\underbrace{101+101+101+\dots+101}_{100 \space times}
=101\cdot 100
\therefore \sum_{n=1}^{100}n=\frac{101\cdot 100}{2}
=5050.
